In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. declares November as National Entrepreneurship Month in the United States. He highlights the importance of entrepreneurs in driving the economy and achieving the American Dream. Despite the challenges faced during the pandemic, there has been a significant increase in new businesses, particularly among minority communities. The American government has provided support through various initiatives such as emergency relief, small business credit programs, and infrastructure investments. The administration aims to create an environment that fosters entrepreneurial success by reducing costs, increasing access to capital and markets, and investing in small business support and STEM education. President Biden emphasizes the resilience, hard work, and vision of entrepreneurs, and encourages Americans to celebrate their contributions.